<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">June 26, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Shipped <code>/cat-cattery-software</code> as page A2 of the 12-page LP cluster plan. Targets the "cattery software" / "cat breeder software" query family without cannibalizing <code>/compare/best-cat-breeding-software</code> (buyer's guide intent) or <code>/compare/best-dog-breeding-software</code> (different species). Reciprocal inbound links wired from <code>/</code>, <code>/for-breeders</code>, <code>/cats</code>, and the cat buyer's guide in the same commit.</p>

  <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      <strong>Why.</strong> Strategy doc (<code>UNIFIED-STRATEGY-2026-06.md</code>) called out species-vertical landing pages as a Cluster A gap. <code>/compare/best-dog-breeding-software</code> proved the format works (134s avg session, 9 striking-distance rankings) but it is dog-only and comparison-shaped. Cat breeders searching "cattery software" or "cat breeder software" had no direct LP — only the comparison page and the species hub, neither of which converts on commercial intent.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>What the page is.</strong> A species-specific, cattery-vocabulary LP for working cat breeders. Mirrors the dog page's structure (breadcrumb, hero + dual CTA, TL;DR aside, workflow pill strip, eight-point rubric, honest-scope band, pricing CTA, FAQ, learn-more, final CTA, sticky mobile CTA, RelatedWorkflows) but uses queen/tom/kitten/queening throughout, references TICA/CFA/ACFA/FIFe instead of AKC/UKC, and uses feline health panels (HCM/PKD/PRA, FeLV/FIV) instead of OFA hips/elbows. Zero "puppy" language per cluster discipline rule 3.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Schema.</strong> WebPage JSON-LD only on-page. FAQPage and BreadcrumbList ride through BaseLayout's <code>faqs</code> + <code>breadcrumbs</code> props (auto-emitted). Deliberately no Article (this is a product LP, not editorial) and no <code>Service.provider=BreederHQ</code> — the Stage 3.5 schema swap is still pending and this page is bundled with that obligation, not ahead of it.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Reciprocal inbound links wired in the same commit</strong> (geographic-reciprocal-backlink rule extended to LP clusters per the plan):
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 ml-2">
      <li><code>/</code> homepage species row — added "Cattery software →" sublink under the Cats card.</li>
      <li><code>/for-breeders</code> in-depth guides list — added bullet pointing to the new page.</li>
      <li><code>/cats</code> learn-more section — added cattery-software link plus a buyer's-guide link to <code>/compare/best-cat-breeding-software</code> (which was missing).</li>
      <li><code>/compare/best-cat-breeding-software</code> TL;DR aside — added sibling sidebar pointing to <code>/cat-cattery-software</code> for visitors with product-intent rather than buyer's-guide intent.</li>
