    <p>
      <strong>Outbound links from the new page</strong> satisfy the per-page contract in the plan: <code>/pricing</code>, <code>/cats</code>, <code>/compare/best-cat-breeding-software</code>, <code>/breeder-management-software</code> (A1 sibling, not yet shipped), <code>/breeder-crm</code> (A4 sibling, not yet shipped), <code>/horse-breeding-software</code> (A3 sibling, not yet shipped), <code>/tools/coefficient-of-inbreeding-calculator</code> (B2, not yet shipped), <code>/trust</code>, and the marketplace. The four sibling LPs are broken-link debt that resolves as Cluster A and B ship per the daily execution sequence.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Anti-cannibalization checks</strong> (cluster discipline rule 1): H1 is "Cattery Software for Working Cat Breeders" — does not contain "best ... software" or any dog-page exact-match term. Page does not include the cross-tool comparison table from <code>/compare</code>. Links OUT to <code>/compare/best-cat-breeding-software</code> as the buyer's-guide handoff.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Trust posture compliance.</strong> Honest-scope section explicitly lists what BreederHQ does not do (does not verify/vet/vouch, does not file registry paperwork, does not provide veterinary services) and links to <code>/trust</code> as "Identity and Credentials" per the legally-locked posture. No "verified cattery" or "verified breeder" claims anywhere on the page.
